AU  - Berger, Michael A.
Y1  - 1983/04/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1983.4284743
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1983.4284743
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 329
EP  - 333
VL  - 8
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The Argyris critique of the case method in executive development programs contains methodological flaws. It omits other factors that might have affected learners' behavior, fails to distinguish between corporate and graduate education, and neglects the positive features of the case method. As a result, his paper raises the important question of whether the case method has limitations for corporate education, but it fails to provide an even-handed, scholarly answer.
AB  - The Argyris critique of the case method in executive development programs contains methodological flaws. It omits other factors that might have affected learners' behavior, fails to distinguish between corporate and graduate education, and neglects the positive features of the case method. As a result, his paper raises the important question of whether the case method has limitations for corporate education, but it fails to provide an even-handed, scholarly answer.
